  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: Myth_79
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 79
  mythName: Myth 79
  omens:
  - '1. Winds bring a sudden dust storm.

    Visibility is short and travel impossible.
    It

    blows over by nightfall.'
  - '2. Farmer staring into the clear sky. Claims

    the air feels too still. Until
    this Myth is

    resolved there is no rain, the land

    gradually dries out,
    rivers start to wither.'
  - '3. Oily buzzards circle above, a band of

    hunters below are playing dead
    in an

    attempt to catch and eat them. These

    birds are usually only found
    in barren

    wastelands.'
  - '4. A disembodied eye floats, watching the

    Knights. If touched it turns
    to dust. The

    hag has taken note of them.'
  - '5. A parched stream, grey dusty earth

    flowing upstream toward the dust
    hag''s

    rocky lair.'
  - '6. In her lair, the dust hag unleashes the

    Desert in full. Every Hex within
    3 Hexes

    of the Myth Hex is now the Desert as long

    as she lives.'
  verse: 
  castEntries:
  - name: Crafty Hunters, Eadon, Frith, Burhow
    statBlock: 'VIG 10, CLA 13, SPI 7, 3 GD

      Shortbow (d6), pig blood, cooking
      pot'
    notes: 
  - name: Oily Buzzard, Grimecrow
    statBlock: 'VIG 7, CLA 14, SPI 2, 2 GD

      Beak (d8), oily hide (any weapons
      that'
    notes: 'wound the creature reduce their die type by

      one size. Can be removed
      with alcohol)'
  - name: The Dust Hag, Exiled from Tomorrow
    statBlock: 'VIG 8, CLA 13, SPI 11, 13 GD

      Claws (2d6), dust shroud (ranged
      attacks are'
    notes: 'Impaired), dust stake (d4, anybody wounded

      is turned to dust until
      the hag dies)

      Driven by her whims (see below).

      Is NOT a Seer.
      Hates any mention of them.

      Flesh and stone and grass are nought but
      falsely forms

      All are dust, nothing more

      WHIMS OF THE DUST HAG

      Wants
      The Catch

      1 Treasure Immediately

      2 Entertainment Of a very specific
      type

      3 Praise At the cost of another

      4 Peace and quiet No amount
      is enough

      5 Authority In another, distant lair

      6 Security Also
      the Seat of Power

      Desert

      Dwelling: Music camp ~ Sanctum: Silent
      stairs ~ Monument: Flower-adorned graves

      Hazard: Bone ridges ~ Curse:
      Eerie drone ~ Ruin: Bloody battlefield

      The'
  flavorTable:
    title: 
    rows: []
  dwelling: Music camp
  sanctum: Silent stairs
  monument: Flower-adorned graves
  hazard: Bone ridges
  curse: Eerie drone
  ruin: Bloody battlefield
  visibleByDefault: 0
